<Layout title="About Me | Bê Acosta" description="Bettina (Bê) Acosta - Senior Technical PM researching agentic commerce, semantic search, and e-commerce architectures.">
  <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-mono); margin-bottom: 2rem; border: none; padding: 0;">
    ℹ️ about_me_
  </h1>

  <section class="about-content">
    <p>
      I'm a <strong>Senior Technical Product Manager</strong> with over 8 years of experience leading digital products and e-commerce infrastructure across Latin America. Right now, my research focuses on <strong>agentic commerce</strong> for my Data Science MBA at USP (ICMC)—specifically, how Google's Gemini models discover, parse, evaluate, and recommend products. This project started when I was analyzing Google Analytics data and saw ChatGPT traffic on a site for the very first time.
    </p>
    <p>
      On Twitter/X, you can find me at <strong>@britneyscripts</strong>. The name stuck after years of writing automation scripts with the help of Stack Overflow, Dev.to, and Reddit. I realized I needed a handle that didn't take itself too seriously. I thought about using <em>QueryLatifah</em>, but <em>britneyscripts</em> perfectly captures my relationship with Python.
    </p>

    <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px dashed var(--border); margin: 2rem 0;" />

    <h3>👻 What I'm Working On: Ghostprod</h3>
    <p>
      I'm building <strong>Ghostprod</strong>, an open-source, multi-agent pipeline that measures the "Semantic Invisibility" of e-commerce Product Detail Pages (PDPs). Currently, I’m working on rebranding it and improving the pipeline using ChromaDB and LangChain.
    </p>
    <p>
      It is the core instrument for my MBA thesis, but it also answers a question nobody is asking yet: <em>when AI agents replace search bars, which e-commerce sites will disappear first?</em> I evaluate PDPs across three core pillars: web performance (CrUX), semantic markup (Schema.org), and NLP parseability.
    </p>

    <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px dashed var(--border); margin: 2rem 0;" />

    <h3>🛠️ The Stack I'm Working With</h3>
    <p>
      I don't have funding for enterprise-grade research infrastructure. Instead, I rely on <strong>Antigravity, Gemini, Google AI Studio, GCP credits, BigQuery, Dataform, Python for everything, local vector databases (ChromaDB), and a USP student account.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      Right now, my focus is on learning RAG, LangChain, embeddings, and vector DBs.
    </p>
    <p>
      It's enough to get the job done. Verifiable data beats marketing gloss.
    </p>

    <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px dashed var(--border); margin: 2rem 0;" />

    <h3>✍️ Why This Blog Exists</h3>
    <p>
      I needed a space outside the walled gardens of LinkedIn and Substack. I wanted somewhere to publish <strong>indexed, searchable content</strong> that shows up when someone searches for "agent readiness" or "SEO for AI agents."
    </p>
    <p>
      This blog is a tribute to the old days of running a WordPress site on localhost, and a manifesto against the Dead Internet, but modernized. It’s static, ultra-fast, and compiles Markdown directly from my Obsidian vault.
    </p>

    <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px dashed var(--border); margin: 2rem 0;" />

    <h3>📚 Background</h3>
    <ul style="list-style: square; margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-top: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>MBA in Data Science</strong> - USP (Brazil)</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>MBA in Software Engineering</strong> - UTFPR (Brazil)</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Postgraduate in Business Data Intelligence</strong> - ESPM (Brazil)</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>MBA in AI for Business</strong> - PUCRS (Brazil)</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Bachelor's in Tourism</strong> - PUCRS (Brazil) - <em>Yes, my background is in tourism! &lt;3</em></li>
    </ul>

    <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--text-muted);">
      I’m a native speaker of Portuguese and Spanish. While I might not write English like Shakespeare yet, I can happily watch Abbott Elementary and The Silence of the Lambs without subtitles, consume a high volume of academic papers in English, and debate architectural trade-offs within Antigravity.
    </p>

